> The tank does not seem too sit level; the forward edge sits on the "shelf" 
> as it should, but the rear rests on the "bellhousing hump" rather than flat 
> on the "shelf". Is this a problem that others have found? What did you do 
> about it or what am I doing wrong?

Hi Joel,
That is why we dent that area to clear the body flange that clears the tranny 
bellhousing.  If this is not done we think that the tank will rub in that 
spot and get a hole in it due to not being properly supported!
